<p><b>Great Britain:</b><br />
4,000 army troops killed in battle (North America only)<br />
27,000 army troops died of disease (North America)<sup id="cite_ref-medical_8-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-medical-8">[8]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-19" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-19">[19]</a></sup><br />
1,243 navy killed in battle, 42,000 deserted, 18,500 died from disease (1776–1780)<sup id="cite_ref-Parliamentary_Register_20-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Parliamentary_Register-20">[20]</a></sup><br />
At least 51,000 dead from all causes</p>
<b>Germans:</b> 1,800 killed in battle<br />
4,888 deserted<br />
7,774 dead from all causes<sup id="cite_ref-medical_8-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-medical-8">[8]</a></sup></td>
